    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/77">Heinricus</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si circa sanctorum loca beneficia condigna
                        inpendimus, hoc nostram regalem maiestatem concedere credimus, insuper et
                        eterna premia nos inde adipisci confidimus. Quapropter omnium Christi
                        nostrorumque fidelium universitatem scire volumus, qualiter nos per
                        interventum dilectissimi nobis <persName key="#Archbishops"
                            ref="#people/1306">Annonis</persName>
                        <orgName>Coloniensis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> nec non ceterorum familiarium
                        nostrorum <rs key="#Monasteries">abbaciam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Rivers #Fisheries #Exemption #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte Marie</orgName> in <placeName
                            ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName> de antecessore nostro imperatore
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">Ottone</persName> a
                            <persName key="#Archbishops" ref="#people/1568">Friderico</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1471">Rauennatis ecclesie</orgName>
                        archiepiscopo iuxta utriusque placitum ad regalis subiectionem proprietatis
                        concambitam ac postea ab Heinrico nostro altero antecessore corroboratam et
                        ab <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/3">Hvgone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchione</rs> magnifice ditatam et in nos
                        successione regni et legali iure hereditatam et ad <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">nostre dominationis manus</rs>
                        receptam cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, quicquid videlicet predicta abbacia
                        per aliquod munimen cartarum vel traditionum retinet vel eidem pertinet ab
                        ecclesia Romana et Rauennate aut ab aliqua alia, seu etiam quicquid iure
                        proprietatis detinet aut acquirere in futuro potuerit, id est totam <rs
                            key="#Islands">insulam</rs> integram a primo latere <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Islands" ref="#places/4657">Pado</placeName> percurrente
                        in <rs key="#Sea">mare</rs>, secundo latere <rs key="#Shores">litus
                            maris</rs>, tertio latere <placeName key="#Rivers #Islands"
                            ref="#places/3596">Gauro</placeName>; et <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscaria</rs> que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2457"><placeName
                                key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/4887">Uolana</placeName></geogName> cum portu integro a
                        rivo <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Badarino</placeName> usque
                        in mare et <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> que dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2454">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Massae #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/3559">Lacus Sanctus</placeName></geogName> cum piscaria
                        que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2455">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Lidini</placeName></geogName>, a primo latere <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundo</rs> qui dicitur <geogName key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/3919"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi">Grecole</placeName></geogName> et fundo qui
                        dicitur <geogName key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/2494"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                ref="#places/3520">Colbea Ceruina</placeName></geogName> et fluvius
                        qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers #Confinia" ref="#places/3568"
                            >Cesi</placeName> et <rs key="#Canals">canale</rs> qui dicitur
                            <placeName key="#Canals #Confinia" ref="#places/3569">Curlo</placeName>,
                        a secundo <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">valle</rs> que dicitur
                            <placeName key="#Confinia #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos" ref="#places/4681"
                            >Farulle</placeName> et fluvio qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Confinia" ref="#places/3564">Conca Agathe</placeName>
                        descendente in Gaurum, a tercio latere ipso Gauro, a qurto Pado percurrente;
                        insuper <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> unam integram que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2487"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                ref="#places/4619">Hustulatus</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Plebs">plebe</rs> sua et aliam que dicitur <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/3920"><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/4695"
                                >Baoria</placeName></geogName> et curtem aliam que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/3921"><placeName key="#Curtes">Ultra
                                Canale</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus ad monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1474">sancte Marie in
                            xenodochio</orgName> pertinentibus, et cum omnibus, que predicte abbatie
                        Hugo marchio filius <persName><name ref="Hubertus">Uberti</name></persName>
                        dedit, quicquid etiam habet aut acquirere potest infra Padum et <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646">Atesin</placeName> fluvium vel infra
                        Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3588">Sandalum</placeName> et
                        quantacumque in apostolice sedis privilegio releguntur, verum etiam queque
                        habet aut acquirere potest in civitate Rauenna in <rs key="#Comitatus"
                            >comitatu</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2449">Comacliense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3538"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2435">Gauellense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/84">Ferariense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/7"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2439">Bononiense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/38"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/208">Mutinense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2409">Cornoliense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3513"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2458">Fauentino</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3515"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2459">Liuiense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/4602"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2480">Pupiliense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1479">Cesenate</geogName></placeName> et in ceteris
                        prope vel longe iacentibus comitatibus cum omni utilitate, que vel nominari
                        vel scribi potest, <rs key="#Exemption">ab omni subiectione archiepiscoporum
                            excutimus</rs>, ut regalis in perpetuum sit nulli dominantium persone
                        subiecta. Sintque <rs key="#Monks">monachi</rs> eius ab omni secularis
                        servicii infestatione securi et ab omni <rs key="#Angaria">angaria</rs> cum
                        suis hominibus remoti; qui de suis qualem voluerint <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbatem</rs> eligant ab episcopo <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1498"
                            >Comacliensi</orgName> consecrandum, qui, si sibi pro pecunia vel aliqua
                        potestate molestus esse voluerit, veniat ad archiepiscopum Rauennatem ab eo
                        benedicendus, et si in hoc istud quod in primo invenerit, ad qualemcunque
                        episcopum voluerit causa consecrationis properet. Si quis autem hoc
                        preceptum infringerit, componat <rs key="#Penalty">ducentas libras auri
                            cocti</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem kamere nostre</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prelibato
                            monasterio</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc regalem paginam manu
                        propria roboratam sigillari iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici (M.) quarti
                        regis. (SI. D.) Sigehardus cancellarius vice Sigefridi archicancellarii
                        recognovi. Data V id. mar. anno dominice incarnationis MLXVI, indictione
                        IIII, anno autem ordinationis domni Heinrici quarti regis XIII, regni vero
                        X; actum Reginbach; feliciter in dei nomine amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
